The paper discusses searching and indexing genomic databases, which involves algorithms and data structures. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the similarity between genomes, which is a topic in computational geometry, making cs.CG (Computational Geometry) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses parameterized complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the history of the idea of searching or indexing only one reference genome, which is a topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
